# Session workflows — hola / adios (all projects)

Use in **every** repository. Copy to `.cursor/rules/hola-adios-global.mdc` and commit.

When the user's message is **only** `hola` / starts with `hola`, or **only** `adios` / starts with
`adios` (case-insensitive), run the matching workflow. Ignore casual Spanish in longer sentences
unless the user clearly intends the workflow.

Always read first if present: `AGENTS.md`, `README.md`, `PROJECT_STATUS.md`, `TODO.md`.

Detect project type from repo contents (do not assume one stack):

| Signal | Project type |
|--------|----------------|
| `index.html` + `assets/` | Static website |
| `package.json` | Node / frontend |
| `pyproject.toml` / `requirements.txt` | Python |
| `Cargo.toml` | Rust |
| Other | Read README for build/test commands |

If the repo has `.cursor/rules/hola-adios-project.mdc`, apply it **after** this file for
project-specific validation and build commands.

---

## hola — start session

Execute in order. Report progress briefly.

### 1. Fetch and check branch status

```bash
git fetch origin
BRANCH="$(git branch --show-current)"
git status -sb
git rev-list --left-right --count "origin/${BRANCH}...HEAD" 2>/dev/null || echo "no-upstream"
```

Interpret `BEHIND<TAB>AHEAD`: behind / ahead / diverged / up to date / no upstream.

### 2. Warn before continuing

| Condition | Warning |
|-----------|---------|
| Behind remote | Branch is N commit(s) behind `origin/<branch>`. Will pull. |
| Ahead of remote | N unpushed commit(s). |
| Diverged | Behind N and ahead M — pull may merge. |
| Uncommitted changes | Pull may fail; list modified files. |
| No upstream | Set upstream or push with `-u`. |

**Stop** if merge conflicts exist (step 4) — do not pull or start dev tools.

### 3. Pull latest

```bash
git pull origin "$(git branch --show-current)"
```

Stop on failure until the user resolves (stash, commit, merge).

### 4. Check merge conflicts

```bash
git diff --name-only --diff-filter=U
git ls-files -u
```

If conflicted: list files, pause hola until resolved.

### 5. Pending branches audit

List remote branches not merged into current branch that may hold missing work:

```bash
git branch -r --no-merged HEAD | grep -v HEAD || true
```

For each branch, briefly note whether it contains assets or features the user might expect on
`main` (e.g. `instagram/`, migrations, config). **Warn** if important folders exist only on
unmerged branches.

### 6. Read status files

Read `PROJECT_STATUS.md` and `TODO.md`. Create from templates if missing (see repo conventions).

### 7. Summarize project status

Include: sync state, warnings, branch, clean/dirty tree, version, last session, open TODOs,
unmerged branches of note, blockers.

### 8. Prepare workspace

Run the dev server / environment defined in the project README or `hola-adios-project.mdc`.
Verify with HTTP or health check when applicable.

### 9. Local machine reminder (mandatory)

The agent runs in **cloud or IDE** — the user's PC is a **separate copy**. Always end hola with
the local PC block.

If `.cursor/rules/hola-adios-project.mdc` defines **Local PC path**, copy that block verbatim
(exact Windows path and CMD commands). Otherwise use:

> **En tu PC:** abre la carpeta del proyecto y ejecuta `git pull origin <branch>`.
> Los cambios solo existen en GitHub hasta que hagas pull.

---

## adios — end session

Execute **all** steps through 8. Commit and push automatically — **no confirmation prompt**.
Fix failures before committing. Do not commit a broken build.

**Goal:** leave GitHub complete, documented, and tell the user exactly how to sync their PC and
what still requires manual action (deploy, FTP, app store, etc.).

### 1. Pending branches — merge or port missing work

Before validation, check for work trapped on feature branches:

```bash
git fetch origin
git branch -r --no-merged "$(git branch --show-current)" | grep -v HEAD || true
```

For each unmerged branch that contains files referenced this session or expected asset folders
(e.g. `instagram/`, `docs/`, migrations):

- **Prefer:** merge or cherry-pick into current branch if safe and scope matches the session.
- **If unsafe:** warn explicitly — list branch name and missing paths; do not pretend adios
  updated everything.

Do **not** leave known asset folders only on side branches when the user expects them on `main`.

### 2. Validation / tests

Run checks appropriate to the project (see project rule or README):

- Static site: required files, link checks, `node --check` on JS if present.
- Node: `npm test` / `npm run lint` if defined in `package.json`.
- Python: `pytest` / `ruff check` if configured.
- Always: run whatever the project's CI would run, or the closest local equivalent.

Report pass/fail per check. Fix failures before continuing.

### 3. Generate build / release artifact

Run the project build script if one exists:

| Project | Typical command |
|---------|-----------------|
| This website | `bash scripts/build_dist_web.sh` |
| Node | `npm run build` |
| Python package | `python -m build` or project script |

Note output path, file count, and size. Record MD5/checksum for primary deliverable when useful.

**Gitignored build output** (e.g. `dist_web/`, `dist/`) is built locally but **not committed**
unless the project explicitly tracks it.

### 4. Asset packs and distributables

If the project maintains offline assets users need on disk (e.g. `instagram/captures/`):

- Verify captures exist and are tracked in git on `main`.
- If a ZIP is used for easy download, regenerate when captures change:

```bash
# Example (adjust paths per project)
zip -r instagram/checkyourbackup-instagram-captures.zip instagram/captures
```

Commit new/changed assets and ZIPs — users pull them; the agent cannot write to their hard drive.

### 5. Update PROJECT_STATUS.md

Update (never skip) with:

- Date (ISO), branch, version
- Session work summary
- Validation results
- Build artifact path, size, checksum
- Unmerged branches resolved or still pending
- Deploy / release status (pending vs done)
- **Local sync reminder** (see step 8)

Update `TODO.md`: mark done items, add follow-ups.

### 6. Show summary of modified files

```bash
git status
git diff --stat
```

List all added/modified/deleted files (excluding gitignored build dirs unless relevant).

### 7. Commit and push

When there are changes:

```bash
git add -A
git commit -m "<clear imperative message summarizing session>"
git push -u origin "$(git branch --show-current)"
```

If nothing to commit, push any unpushed commits. Retry push on network errors (4 attempts,
exponential backoff).

### 8. Final report (mandatory)

Always include this block:

#### GitHub (done by adios)

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| Branch | |
| Commit | |
| Push | success / failed |
| Validation | pass / fail |
| Build | path, files, size |

#### Your PC — you must do this

> **adios actualiza GitHub, no tu disco local.**

If `hola-adios-project.mdc` has a **Local PC path** section, paste that entire block here
(exact path `C:\Users\...`, CMD commands, Instagram folders). Do not replace with generic text.

Otherwise:

> En la carpeta del proyecto en tu PC:
> ```cmd
> git checkout main
> git pull origin main
> ```

| Asset | Path in repo (after pull) |
|-------|---------------------------|
| (project-specific) | see hola-adios-project.mdc |

#### Manual actions (not automated by adios)

- [ ] `git pull` on local PC
- [ ] Deploy / FTP / hosting upload (if applicable)
- [ ] Purge CDN cache (if applicable)
- [ ] App store / release publish (if applicable)

List only what applies to this project.

